      div.page-header
        h1 Interactive Online Biology
      p.
        Interactive Online Biology Lab is an active research project at #[a(href="http://web.stanford.edu/group/riedel-kruse/index.html") Riedel-Kruse Lab] at Stanford University
        as part of a Ph.D thesis of #[a(href="http://cs.stanford.edu/~zhossain") Zahid Hossain]. The goal of the project is to develop technologies to provide
        interactive access to a real biology lab over the Internet at scale for concurrent users and compare with simulated labs. This involves designing and implementing custom hardware, Biotic Processing Units (BPU),
        software infrastructure with distributed computing and user friendly interfaces.

      p.
        In this particular online lab, we provide a means to study the underlying principles of phototaxis of a single celled micro-organism called #[a(href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euglena") Euglena Gracilis] through
        a simulated environment.
